{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17506062","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17506062"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:39:54+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:39:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2512"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17583281","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17583281"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:11:48+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:11:48+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2512"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2512","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2512"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.5,0.19,0.07,0.2]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2512"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102681"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2512","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2512"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2512"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85162"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"43"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"377"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4985"},{"type":"tags","id":"5249"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"},{"type":"tags","id":"8149"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11634"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"2329"},{"type":"contributions","id":"2418"},{"type":"contributions","id":"15333"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17189"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35998"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44781"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45073"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102681","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/102681"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 65-year-old woman is being assessed for the management of a recently diagnosed breast cancer. After noticing a lump in her left breast she had a follow-up mammography which revealed an irregular mass with microcalcifications. A core biopsy showed cellular proliferation with invasion of the basement membrane. A CT scan of the abdomen and thorax revealed no evidence of distant metastases. The breast tumour is oestrogen receptor (ER) positive. Her last menstrual period was 14 years ago. The physician considers the use of adjuvant letrozole as part of her treatment and the potential complications are considered.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Of which of the following would she be most at risk with the addition of this adjuvant therapy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Neutropaenia","Osteoporosis","Deep vein thrombosis","Dilated cardiomyopathy","Endometrial cancer"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient is a postmenopausal woman with biopsy-proven, oestrogen hormone-receptor sensitive breast cancer. Aromatase inhibitors such as anastrozole and letrozole are medications used to target such breast cancers. This class of drugs work by reducing the conversion of androstenedione to estrone and decreasing the conversion of testosterone to oestradiol, thereby decreasing tumour growth. Side effects of aromatase inhibitors include an increased risk of \u003Cstrong\u003Eosteoporosis\u003C/strong\u003E, vaginal dryness, hot flushes and night sweats.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIncreased risk of thromboembolic events such as \u003Cstrong\u003Edeep vein thrombosis \u003C/strong\u003Eand pulmonary embolism, as well as \u003Cstrong\u003Eendometrial cancer \u003C/strong\u003Eare side effects of tamoxifen. It works as a competitive antagonist on oestrogen receptors of the breast, thereby decreasing breast tumour growth, however works as an agonist on the oestrogen receptors in the endometrium; encouraging proliferation and risk of endometrial cancer. Tamoxifen is an adjuvant therapy for premenopausal women with biopsy-proven, oestrogen hormone-receptor sensitive breast cancer.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDilated cardiomyopathy\u003C/strong\u003E and other cardiotoxic effects are side effects of trastuzumab (herceptin). It is a humanised monoclonal antibody against the HER2 tyrosine kinase receptor, used as adjuvant therapy for biopsy-proven HER2 positive breast cancers.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENeutropaenia\u003C/strong\u003E is not a side effect of aromatase inhibitors.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["There is an increased risk of osteoporosis with aromatase inhibitors."],"references":["Smith IE, Dowsett M. Aromatase inhibitors in breast cancer. N Engl J Med 2003; 348:2431. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/12802030/","Geisler J, Haynes B, Anker G, et al. Influence of letrozole and anastrozole on total body aromatization and plasma estrogen levels in postmenopausal breast cancer patients evaluated in a randomized, cross-over study. J Clin Oncol 2002; 20:751. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/11821457/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85162"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2512"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85162","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/85162"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"